A tragic incident occurred when a bridge over the Mississippi River in Minneapolis collapsed, causing cars and trucks to plunge into the water.
Despite the chaos, a school bus with children narrowly avoided disaster.
The collapse resulted in at least six deaths, with ongoing search efforts.
Authorities confirmed no terrorism involvement.
The bridge, built in 1967, had structural issues dating back to 1990.
President Bush pledged federal support for rebuilding.
The state initiated inspections of similar bridges.
The community mourns the lives lost and the impact of this devastating event.
